# References and Attributions



## History

This course was first taught by Michael Musick at the University of Montana in the Spring of 2018.



## Content



Additional material has been linked from or adapted from;

- [scotch.io](https:scotch.io)
- Wikipedia Articles for general information



## Website Template

The course website has been adapted and built from [P2PU.org's](http://howto.p2pu.org), [course-in-a-box](https://github.com/p2pu/course-in-a-box/) and their [Jekyll Course template](http://github.com/p2pu/jekyll-course-template).





## Plugin, Libraries, and Packages

The live reloading and code editing capabilities are capable through the use of [Jotted](https://ghinda.net/jotted/). This creates an "environment for showcasing self-hosted HTML, CSS and JavaScript snippets, with editable source."
